defaultProfessor Margetts:default 
default“
defaultOpen data
default”
default is an interesting term and it gets many terms bundled into it.  In some ways, open data is a bit like the little white bunny of 
defaultg
defaultovernment.  It means something nice, warm and good that will aid democracy.  It is a confused term
default,
default though
default,
default because it implies that it is just opening data up for public use.  In the loosest sense
default,
default that would be a term
default,
default 
defaultbut 
defaultsome people use 
defaultit 
defaultto mean open government; some people use it to mean big data
default—
defaultdata that can be used for a particular kind of analysis.  
defaultThe confusion comes from the fact that it basically has three aims
default,
default and you will see all these aims mentioned by different people
default—
defaultand even the same people.  
defaultThey are: greater transparency; 
defaultimproving 
defaultg
defaultovernment
